    "Html": "\r\n<p>Hi,</p>\r\n<p>I'm confused about the xaml support for DataTemplate'd LineGraph objects in D3.</p>\r\n<p>I'd like to add a class PointsGraphItemsControl than derives from ItemsControl (and implements IPlotterElement) to specify a ItemTemplate that has a LineGraph correctly bound to my view model. However when I add this to a ChartPlotter the template is never\r\n instanticated.</p>\r\n<p>It seems this is because although Plotter is a ContentControl it has the attribute\r\n</p>\r\n<div style=\"color:black; background-color:white\">\r\n<pre>[ContentProperty(<span style=\"color:#a31515\">&quot;Children&quot;</span>)]\r\n</pre>\r\n</div>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>Is there any way to force the template to be created?</p>\r\n<p>I will post more when I understand the problem a bit better.</p>\r\n<p>regards,</p>\r\n<p>Danny</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<div style=\"color:black; background-color:white\">\r\n<pre><span style=\"color:blue\">&lt;</span><span style=\"color:#a31515\">c</span><span style=\"color:blue\">:</span><span style=\"color:#a31515\">ChartPlotter</span> <span style=\"color:red\">Name</span><span style=\"color:blue\">=</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:blue\">plotter</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:black\"></span><span style=\"color:blue\">&gt;</span>\r\n\r\n    <span style=\"color:blue\">&lt;</span><span style=\"color:#a31515\">v</span><span style=\"color:blue\">:</span><span style=\"color:#a31515\">PointsGraphItemsControl</span> <span style=\"color:red\">ItemsSource</span><span style=\"color:blue\">=</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:blue\">{Binding Path=Graphs}</span><span style=\"color:black\">&quot;</span><span style=\"color:blue\">&gt;</span>\r\n        <span style=\"color:blue\">&lt;</span><span style=\"color:#a31515\">v</span><span style=\"color:blue\">:</span><span style=\"color:#a31515\">PointsGraphItemsControl.ItemTemplate</span><spa